  "descriptions": [
    {
      "text": "Smash TV is a twin-stick shooter developed and published by Williams Electronics as an arcade video game in 1990. It was designed by Eugene Jarvis and programmed by Mark Turmell, with similar gameplay to Jarvis' earlier game Robotron: 2084 (1982). The Super Nintendo Entertainment System, Sega Genesis, Master System and Game Gear versions are titled Super Smash TV.",
      "lang": "en",
      "source": "wikipedia_en"
